<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<%- include('partials/head', { title: 'Glossary' }) %>
<body>
  <%- include('partials/header') %>

  <section class="track-hero-v2">
    <div class="container">
      <h1 class="track-hero-v2__title">Glossary</h1>
      <p class="track-hero-v2__subtitle">Key terms and concepts referenced throughout this workshop</p>
      <div class="glossary-search">
        <div class="glossary-search__input-wrapper">
          <i class="ph ph-magnifying-glass glossary-search__icon"></i>
          <input
            type="text"
            id="glossary-filter"
            class="glossary-search__input"
            placeholder="Search terms..."
            autocomplete="off"
          >
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="glossary-page section">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="glossary-page__count" id="glossary-count">Showing all 20 terms</p>

      <div class="glossary-grid" id="glossary-grid">

        <div class="glossary-item" data-term="activation">
          <h4 class="glossary-item__term">Activation</h4>
          <p class="glossary-item__definition">The process of pushing segment data from Data 360 to downstream systems like Marketing Cloud, advertising platforms, or data warehouses for campaign execution and targeting.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="glossary-item" data-term="calculated insights">
          <h4 class="glossary-item__term">Calculated Insights</h4>
          <p class="glossary-item__definition">Custom metrics derived from Data 360 data using SQL queries. They compute aggregated values (like lifetime value or engagement scores) and attach them to unified profiles for segmentation and activation.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="glossary-item" data-term="data actions">
          <h4 class="glossary-item__term">Data Actions</h4>
          <p class="glossary-item__definition">Automated triggers in Data 360 that fire when specific data conditions are met, enabling real-time responses through Platform Events, Flows, or external webhooks.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="glossary-item" data-term="data cloud">
          <h4 class="glossary-item__term">Data 360</h4>
          <p class="glossary-item__definition">Salesforce's hyperscale data platform that unifies customer data from any source in real time, creating a single view of the customer. It powers segmentation, activation, analytics, and AI across the Salesforce ecosystem.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="glossary-item" data-term="data model object">
          <h4 class="glossary-item__term">Data Model Object (DMO)</h4>
          <p class="glossary-item__definition">A standardized schema in Data 360 that data is mapped to during ingestion. DMOs provide a canonical data model that enables cross-source querying and unification.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="glossary-item" data-term="data space">
          <h4 class="glossary-item__term">Data Space</h4>
          <p class="glossary-item__definition">A logical partition within Data 360 that provides data isolation between brands, business units, or regions while sharing the same underlying infrastructure.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="glossary-item" data-term="data stream">
          <h4 class="glossary-item__term">Data Stream</h4>
          <p class="glossary-item__definition">A connection that ingests data from a source system into Data 360. Types include CRM streams (Salesforce objects), connector streams (external APIs), and file-based streams (S3, SFTP).</p>
        </div>

        <div class="glossary-item" data-term="einstein ai segments">
          <h4 class="glossary-item__term">Einstein AI Segments</h4>
          <p class="glossary-item__definition">Segments created using natural language prompts processed by Einstein AI. Users describe their target audience in plain English, and AI translates it into segment filter criteria.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="glossary-item" data-term="identity resolution">
          <h4 class="glossary-item__term">Identity Resolution</h4>
          <p class="glossary-item__definition">The process of matching and merging records from multiple data sources to create a single unified profile for each individual. Uses match rules (exact, fuzzy, probabilistic) to resolve identities.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="glossary-item" data-term="metadata studio">
          <h4 class="glossary-item__term">Metadata Studio</h4>
          <p class="glossary-item__definition">A tool within Data 360 for cataloging, classifying, and governing data assets. Provides data lineage visualization and helps organizations understand their data landscape.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="glossary-item" data-term="platform event">
          <h4 class="glossary-item__term">Platform Event</h4>
          <p class="glossary-item__definition">A Salesforce messaging mechanism that enables real-time communication between systems. Data 360 Data Actions can publish platform events that trigger Flows or external processes.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="glossary-item" data-term="profile explorer">
          <h4 class="glossary-item__term">Profile Explorer</h4>
          <p class="glossary-item__definition">A Data 360 interface for viewing unified customer profiles, including merged source records, related data, calculated insights, and segment memberships in a single timeline view.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="glossary-item" data-term="segment">
          <h4 class="glossary-item__term">Segment</h4>
          <p class="glossary-item__definition">A defined subset of unified profiles that meet specific criteria. Segments are built using filters on attributes, behaviors, and calculated insights, then published for activation.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="glossary-item" data-term="unified individual">
          <h4 class="glossary-item__term">Unified Individual</h4>
          <p class="glossary-item__definition">The master profile entity in Data 360 that represents a single person after identity resolution has merged records from multiple sources. It is the primary entity for segmentation and activation.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="glossary-item" data-term="data explorer">
          <h4 class="glossary-item__term">Data Explorer</h4>
          <p class="glossary-item__definition">A query interface within Data 360 that allows users to explore data model objects, run ad-hoc queries, filter records, and visualize data relationships without writing SQL.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="glossary-item" data-term="data governance">
          <h4 class="glossary-item__term">Data Governance</h4>
          <p class="glossary-item__definition">Policies and controls applied to Data 360 data including field classification, sensitivity labels, consent management, and access controls to ensure compliance with regulations like GDPR.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="glossary-item" data-term="document ai">
          <h4 class="glossary-item__term">Document AI</h4>
          <p class="glossary-item__definition">An AI-powered capability in Data 360 that extracts structured data from unstructured documents (PDFs, images, forms) and maps it to data model objects for unification.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="glossary-item" data-term="agentforce">
          <h4 class="glossary-item__term">Agentforce</h4>
          <p class="glossary-item__definition">Salesforce's AI-powered platform that enables organizations to build, deploy, and manage autonomous AI agents capable of taking actions across Salesforce applications and external systems.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="glossary-item" data-term="personalization">
          <h4 class="glossary-item__term">Personalization</h4>
          <p class="glossary-item__definition">A Data 360 capability that delivers individualized content and experiences based on real-time behavioral data, profile attributes, and AI-powered recommendations across web and app channels.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="glossary-item" data-term="activation target">
          <h4 class="glossary-item__term">Activation Target</h4>
          <p class="glossary-item__definition">A configured destination system where segment data is sent. Targets include Marketing Cloud, Google Ads, Meta, S3 buckets, and other connected platforms for campaign execution.</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <%- include('partials/footer') %>
  <script src="/js/app.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
